1. Product Overview

Product name: Flo App
Type: Menstrual cycle tracking app
Goal: Help users track their periods, see them on a calendar, get simple predictions, and view basic cycle analysis ‚Äî all offline on their device.

2. MVP Objectives

The MVP should allow a user to:

Log period start and end dates

View these logs on a calendar

See a predicted next period date

View basic analysis (average cycle length, average period length, last cycle summary, regular/irregular)

Manage a simple profile (age + dark mode theme)

No login, no backend, all data stored locally.

3. Epics Summary
Epic ID	Epic Name	Short Description
E1	Period Tracking	Log, edit, delete period data with confirmations
E2	Calendar	Visual calendar with highlighted period and predicted days
E3	Predictions	Estimate and show the next period date
E4	Analysis	Show key stats and regularity of cycles
E5	Profile	Basic user preferences (age, theme)
4. Detailed Epics & User Stories
üü• Epic E1 ‚Äì Period Tracking

Goal: Let users keep accurate and clean period data.

Story E1-S1 ‚Äì Edit Period Start Date
As a user, I want to edit my period start date so that the app can give accurate predictions.

Story Points: 3

Acceptance Criteria:

User can change the start date of a logged period.

Updated date is saved in local storage.

Calendar view reflects the updated date.

Predictions update based on the new date.

A success message is shown after updating.

Story E1-S2 ‚Äì Delete Wrong Period Log
As a user, I want to delete a wrong period log so that my cycle data stays clean and predictions stay correct.

Story Points: 2

Acceptance Criteria:

User can see a list or view where a period log can be selected.

User can delete a log only after a confirmation step.

Deleted logs no longer appear in the calendar or analysis.

Predictions recalculate without that log.

A success message confirms deletion.

Story E1-S3 ‚Äì Confirmation After Logging
As a user, I want to see a confirmation message after logging my period so that I know it was saved successfully.

Story Points: 1

Acceptance Criteria:

After logging start or end date, a small confirmation message is shown.

The message disappears automatically after a short time.

The new log is immediately visible on the calendar.

