üü¶ Epic E3 ‚Äì Predictions

Goal: Show a simple next period prediction based on past data.

Story E3-S1 ‚Äì Next Expected Period Date
As a user, I want to see my next expected period date so that I can plan ahead.

Story Points: 3

Acceptance Criteria:

App calculates a predicted next period start date.

The prediction is visible on the home or main screen.

If there is not enough data, an informative message is shown instead.

Story E3-S2 ‚Äì Use Past Cycles for Estimation
As a user, I want the app to use my past cycles to estimate my next cycle so that predictions are personalised.

Story Points: 2

Acceptance Criteria:

App calculates cycle lengths from logged cycles.

An average cycle length is computed from available data.

Logic works even with only 1‚Äì2 cycles, though it may be less accurate.

Story E3-S3 ‚Äì Highlight Predicted Dates on Calendar
As a user, I want predicted dates highlighted in a different colour so that I can easily separate predictions from real logs.

Story Points: 2

Acceptance Criteria:

Predicted dates are visually distinct from actual logged periods.

A small legend or label explains the meaning of the predicted colour.

When prediction changes, the highlight updates.

Story E3-S4 ‚Äì Auto-Update Predictions
As a user, I want predictions to update automatically when I edit any period dates so that results stay accurate.

Story Points: 1

Acceptance Criteria:

Any edit or deletion of period logs triggers recalculation.

Updated prediction appears without needing app restart.

üü™ Epic E4 ‚Äì Analysis

Goal: Provide simple but useful cycle insights.

Story E4-S1 ‚Äì Average Cycle Length
As a user, I want to see my average cycle length so that I can understand my overall pattern.

Story Points: 2

Acceptance Criteria:

App computes cycle length between period starts.

Shows the average in days (e.g. ‚ÄúAverage cycle length: 28 days‚Äù).

